Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Halve,
peel and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Peel and finely dice @carrots{2}(peeled and finely diced). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Roughly
chop @button mushrooms{4%oz}(roughly chopped). Slice @sweet Italian pork sausage{18%oz} into thick coins.

Heat @olive oil{4%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion, carrot, and
garlic to pan and cook until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Toss in mushrooms and
sausage and cook until mushrooms have softened and sausage is lightly browned,
about ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While veggies cook, add @spaghetti{12%oz} to boiling water and cook until al
dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain, reserving 1 cup of cooking water.

Stir @crushed tomatoes{2%box}, 1 cup pasta cooking water, and @chicken stock concentrate{1} into pan. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt
and pepper.

Stir @spinach{10%oz} into pan with Bolognese and let wilt.

> TIP: If Bolognese is not saucy or seems stiff, add an extra splash of water.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Roughly chop @parsley{¼%oz}(roughly chopped). Divide spaghetti between plates and
top with Bolognese. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{½%cup} and parsley.